#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:4
msgid "Instrument Modes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:6
msgid ""
"Once you are familiar with the way the MidiGurdy works, you can customise"
" it's behaviour and extend the capabilities of the instrument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:9
msgid ""
"The different instrument modes allow you to configure the **number of "
"strings** in your MidiGurdy and the behaviour of the **lid buttons** S1 "
"S2 S3 and Mod1 Mod2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:18
msgid "The lid buttons affected by the instrument mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:20
msgid "The following modes are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:23
msgid "3 Strings (the default mode)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:25
msgid ""
"This is the default mode of the MidiGurdy. It provides one melody, one "
"drone and one trompette string."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:28
msgid "**Lid Buttons with 3 Strings**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:30
msgid ""
"S1, S2, S3 are used to switch the drone, melody and trompette strings on "
"/ off."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:31
msgid "Mod1 and Mod2 can be used to load the previous and next preset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:37
msgid "The home screen in \"3 Strings\" mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:41
msgid "6 Strings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:43
msgid ""
"This mode gives you an additional set of melody, drone and trompette "
"strings, bringing the MidiGurdy to a toal of 6 strings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:46
msgid "**Lid Buttons with 6 Strings**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:48 ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:96
msgid ""
"S1, S2, S3 are used to switch the drone, melody and trompette of the "
"**current set** on / off."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:49
msgid ""
"Mod1 loads the previous preset with a **long press**, the next preset "
"with a **short press**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:50
msgid "Mod2 switches which **string set** the S1, S2 and S3 buttons control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:52
msgid "**Home Screen with 6 Strings**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:54
msgid ""
"The home screen uses a different layout in two strings mode. It shows two"
" rows of strings, each row represents one **string set**. Which string "
"set is active is shown by the vertical lines next to the string "
"indicators."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:62
msgid "The home screen in 6 String mode with the first string set active"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:69
msgid "The home screen in 6 String mode with the second string set active"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:71
msgid "**String Menus with 6 Strings**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:73
msgid ""
"As you now have two strings of each type, you also have two string menus "
"each. For example, pressing D2 will open the first melody string menu, "
"pressing D2 again will switch to the second melody string menu. Which "
"string you are currently editing is shown in on the left."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:81
msgid "The two string menu indicators after pressing D2 repeatedly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:85
msgid "9 Strings, grouped by number"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:87
msgid ""
"The 9 Strings mode gives you yet another additional set of melody, drone "
"and trompette strings, bringing the MidiGurdy to a toal of 9 strings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:90
msgid ""
"The first variant of the 9 Strings modes groupes the strings by number, "
"just like the 6 strings mode but with one additional set. The lid buttons"
" work slightly different though:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:94
msgid "**Lid Buttons with 9 Strings, grouped by number**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:97
msgid "Switch between sets with **short presses** on Mod1 and Mod2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:98
msgid "Switch between presets with **long presses** on Mod1 and Mod2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:100 ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:157
msgid "**Home Screen with 9 Strings, grouped by number**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:102
msgid ""
"The home screen uses a similar layout to the 6 strings mode. It shows "
"three rows of strings, each row represents one **string set**. Which "
"string set is active is shown by the vertical lines next to the string "
"indicators."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:110
msgid ""
"The home screen in 9 Strings, grouped by number mode with the first "
"string set active"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:116
msgid ""
"The home screen in 9 Strings, grouped by number mode with the second "
"string set active"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:122
msgid ""
"The home screen in 9 Strings, grouped by number mode with the third "
"string set active"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:125
msgid "**String Menus with 9 Strings**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:127
msgid ""
"The string menus gain an additional entry, just as with the 6 String "
"mode. So for example, pressing D2 will open the first melody string menu,"
" pressing D2 again will switch to the second melody string menu. and "
"pressing D2 a third time switches to the third melody string menu. Which "
"string you are currently editing is shown in on the left."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:137
msgid "The three string menu indicators after pressing D2 repeatedly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:141
msgid "9 Strings, grouped by type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:143
msgid ""
"This mode gives you nine strings, just like the previous mode. But it "
"groupes the strings in a different way. This only affects how you switch "
"strings on and off using the S1 S2 S3 buttons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:147
msgid ""
"Grouping by string type means that S1 S2 S3 switch the first, second and "
"third string of the currently active type. If the currently active set is"
" \"melody\", then S1 switches melody 1, S2 melody 2 and S3 melody 3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:151
msgid "**Lid Buttons with 9 Strings, grouped by type**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:153
msgid ""
"S1, S2, S3 are used to switch strings 1 - 3 or the **currrently active "
"type**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:154
msgid "Switch between presets **short or long presses** on Mod1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:155
msgid "Switch the active string type with **short or long presses** on Mod2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:163
msgid ""
"The home screen in 9 Strings, grouped by type mode with the drone set "
"active"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:169
msgid ""
"The home screen in 9 Strings, grouped by number mode with the melody set "
"active"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:175
msgid ""
"The home screen in 9 Strings, grouped by number mode with the trompette "
"set active"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:178
msgid "Old MidiGurdy Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:180
msgid ""
"This is the way the MidiGurdy worked before configurable instrument modes"
" were added: 9 strings, grouped by number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:183
msgid "**Lid Buttons**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:185
msgid ""
"S1, S2, S3 are used to switch the drone, melody and trompette of the "
"**current set** on /off."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:186
msgid "**Hold** Mod1 to select the second set"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:187
msgid "**Hold** Mod2 to select the third set"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:189
msgid "(If you don't hold Mod1 or Mod2, the first set is active.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:192
msgid "Custom Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Instrument_Modes.rst:194
msgid ""
"If you would like a different instrument setup that is not offered by "
"these predefined modes, you can also open the :ref:`web-interface` and "
"choose a custom setup of strings and how the lid buttons react in the "
"\"Settings\" area."
msgstr ""

